# SolidWorks – 3D Printed Winding Mechanism

## Overview
This folder contains SolidWorks parts and assemblies for the winding mechanism of our elevator building model. All components were designed in SolidWorks and fabricated via 3D printing.

## What We Built
The **winding mechanism** that drives the elevator car up and down the building shaft. This includes the spool, housing, and any structural brackets needed to mount the system to the building frame.

## Why SolidWorks
SolidWorks enabled us to model complex 3D geometry with precise fits and tolerances, which was critical for a functional mechanism with moving parts. The parametric design tools allowed us to iterate quickly and ensure all printed components assembled correctly.

## File Formats
| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `.SLDPRT` | Native SolidWorks part files |
| `.SLDASM` | Native SolidWorks assembly file |
| `.STL` | Export format used for 3D printing (renders in GitHub) |
| `.STEP` | Universal CAD format for interoperability |

## Tools & Process
- **Software:** SolidWorks
- **Fabrication method:** 3D printing (FDM)
- **Workflow:** 3D modeling → STL export → Slicing → 3D print

